[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring harness configuration**\n\nI'm wondering if this harness auto-generates resources from the JVM agent during the workflow. The build.gradle doesn't have metadataCopy in the agent configuration, so I'm thinking about the TCK native compile — could that include agent output from javaTest? It's a bit unclear to me right now. As for existing tasks, \"nativeTestCompile\" might use test resources and metadata from the metadata/ directory instead of the agent. Perhaps the full `test` runs the JVM with the agent and utilizes the output.\n\n**Exploring library class names**\n\nI’m thinking about using existing public library class names for dynamic methods. For instance, HikariConfig(Properties) tests setter reflection on HikariConfig itself, but I need the metadata for the library class. There’s limited support for reflection, except for TestSQLExceptionOverride or CredentialsProvider, so I might skip the class name provider.\n\nAlternatively, PropertyElf could set HikariConfig properties, which would avoid the need for MutableBean and support reflection. That seems like a more efficient route!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_024569182bc7a96d0169f64e5a904c81a1a5a4cf8521a8cd34\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9k5uyQ1Ceyg4ear1kmtP-sAqg3ciMb6tb_z-5iaA40qZTXI9VfPBa80rIxCPNJe0JNJHtBFb6Ci7H8_FDoSJrsjnUNfKHxL08JhvgeYFZl5QOJjLv6m5-sOTYN9QV6UKsVSfVBpQSO3hLxfGZr1hBfKC7yHb0tr3zCsHuyf7FsOFk12L6gy1GQRrsdP-EWvlLfvmKqCnibc8MHxje-oJ1TzqoyJxau4aKI_HUzR_lXUddL6KXK_qF9G6eWDheKCpnK1qIH5-407VeVsq5hbz-4-F589tCvSwbTspdgYy2fdWYl6dEczNcNrliIQG1cYakBhZzHqnRbrqyW17e2g4XFLADoVOvKsGynqq4EraU_41QLJRf0Ks6NZSU3uLQC7hNwPInahDo0EhAG_BXR7aOCctcZ2-yqh5opMJzQAbjVALWNV1cX_dGhoDH_QgfT84ZyZWYDMtxejU-jIOoWi9WW83z7rTfVSyqN6eyKuzZR6jwdJMIZ8QAj8jdUy0iVi5YI8NgmMCLTf3ynnIE1UMKVgQwTqekoF0qN5jEajR3xj1091GIPPKNLPVa3iLo7bbwQiHwOwqd6AycKgkmS9ku8xq0Rw3X4-dWVC_6rdDIiQGxk7zRI4sjbr2C