erates resources from the JVM agent during the workflow. The build.gradle doesn't have metadataCopy in the agent configuration, so I'm thinking about the TCK native compile — could that include agent output from javaTest? It's a bit unclear to me right now. As for existing tasks, \\\"nativeTestCompile\\\" might use test resources and metadata from the metadata/ directory instead of the agent. Perhaps the full `test` runs the JVM with the agent and utilizes the output.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring library class names**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using existing public library class names for dynamic methods. For instance, HikariConfig(Properties) tests setter reflection on HikariConfig itself, but I need the metadata for the library class. There’s limited support for reflection, except for TestSQLExceptionOverride or CredentialsProvider, so I might skip the class name provider.\\n\\nAlternatively, PropertyElf could set HikariConfig properties, which would avoid the need for MutableBean and support reflection. That seems like a more efficient route!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yNjHlCz4CsDUBvMArOOUTVZs|fc_024569182bc7a96d0169f64e6ecd6c81a181b4c5ad50bffdc2", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.zaxxer/HikariCP/7.0.2/src/test/java/com/zaxxer/hikaricp/test/HikariDataSourceTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        RecordingDataSource configuredDataSource = RecordingDataSource.lastInstance();\n        assertThat(configuredDataSource.getServerName()).isEqualTo(\"db.example.test\");", "newText": "        RecordingDataSource configuredDataSource = RecordingDataSource.lastInstance();\n        assertThat(configuredDataSource).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(configuredDataSource.getServerName()).isEqualTo(\"db.example.test\");"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1525, "output": 1432, "cacheRead": 54272, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57229, "cost": {"input": 0, "output"